source: https://www.hellofresh.co.nz/recipes/easy-hawaiian-bacon-and-pineapple-tortilla-pizza-6479b1d5566de4b9070ed35e
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 15 minutes
---

1 olive oil
1 tin Pineapple Slices
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet diced bacon
1 bag Deluxe Salad Mix
½ tin Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic & Olive Oil
1 packet Smoked Cheddar Cheese
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Drain pineapple slices and roughly chop.

• Spread crushed & sieved tomatoes (see ingredients) evenly across the mini flourtortillas using the back of a spoon.
• Sprinkle with smoked Cheddar cheese and shredded Cheddar cheese. Top with pineapple and diced bacon.

• Place the tortilla pizzas directly on wire oven racks and bake until the cheese is melted and golden, 4-5 minutes.
• Meanwhile, add deluxe salad mix, a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper in a medium bowl. Toss to combine.

TIP: Placing tortillas directly on wire rack helps base to crisp up.

• Divide Hawaiian bacon and pineapple tortilla pizza between plates.
• Serve with deluxe salad. Enjoy!